{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 1: Deriving a network from text is an important task in several application domains, with several tools originating from research communities including educational technology, modeling & simulation, or forecasting.",
    "Once a network is obtained, it can be used as a visual aid or analyzed.",
    "To situate this paper within the literature, our techniques and data sources are underlined and colored in green.",
    "In this paper, we propose an approach to derive causal maps from text using GPT 3.5 as a PLM and we evaluate it on white papers by contrast to human-generated causal maps on the same topics.",
    "Our main contributions are twofold: 1 We perform prompt-engineering to guide GPT in identifying causal relationships and we empirically devise a set of 12 filters to extract results in a conservative manner that limits the risk of false-positives."
  ]
}